<subsection xml:id="subsec-code-parking">
  <title>Code</title>
  <term>Source Code</term>
  <program>
    int IR1 = 2;//declare  IR1 sensor
    int IR2 = 3; //declare  IR2 sensor
    int LED1 = 5; //declare  LED1
    int LED2 = 6; //declare  LED2
    void setup()
    {
      Serial.begin(9600);//initialize the serial communication 
      pinMode(LED1, OUTPUT);//mode declaration for LED1
      pinMode(LED2, OUTPUT); //mode declaration for LED2
      pinMode(IR1, INPUT); //mode declaration for IR1
      pinMode(IR2, INPUT); //mode declaration for IR2
    }
    void loop() {
      if (digitalRead(IR1) == HIGH)//when the state is high
        {
          digitalWrite(LED1, HIGH);//set led1 to high
          Serial.println("Slot 2 is free");//print slot2 is free
        }
      if ( digitalRead(IR2) == HIGH) //when the IR2 state is high
        {
          digitalWrite(LED2, HIGH);// set led2 to high
          Serial.println(" Slot 1 is free") //print slot1 is free
        }
      else
        {
          Serial.println(" Wait");
        }
    }    
  </program>
  <term>Code Explanation </term>
  <ol> 
<li>
  <p>
    In void setup function Declaring 2nd and 3rd pins of IR sensor respectively. 
  </p>
</li>
<li>
  <p>
    Initializing the IR sensor as input using pinMode function 
  </p>
</li>
<li>
  <p>
    Two Led is connected to the pin of 5th  and 6th  through 1K ohm resistor
  </p>
</li>
<li>
  <p>
    In void loop function the value of IR sensor will be stored as digital data using digital Read function
  </p>
</li>
<li>
  <p>
    When the sensor data is high, the LED will be high, message in the serial monitor will be displayed to indicate the user which slot is free.
  </p>
</li>
  </ol>
